comment_data.body:
Unless I'm missing the point of the comment, the varobject struct is almost inevitably:

```
struct {
    ...
    ItemType items[0];
};
```
or

```
struct {
    ...
    ItemType items[1];
};
```
or
```
struct {
    ...
    ItemType items[];
};
```
So the calculation of "is the struct size right" is based on there either being 0 or 1 items. Obviously extra space may be allocated at runtime for more items, but doesn't need considering here

